<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-209E8DDD-E478-4E6A-8F22-EEA85DF86599" version="1" lang="en-US"?><reference xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-209E8DDD-E478-4E6A-8F22-EEA85DF86599" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic reference)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c reference oceReference-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic       reference/reference "><title class="- topic/title ">04 Printhead specifications: transport and storage conditions</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148565-B31"><p class="- topic/p ">This document gives you information of the new printhead transport and storage conditions.</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-DF97BEA1-D9B8-4E89-BBDD-213F22952961" type="important"><p class="- topic/p ">The nozzle performance is badly influenced when the printhead is exposed to high temperatures (above 60 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Celsius, (140 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Fahrenheit) over a longer period of time (&gt; 2 weeks).</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Specifications</category></metadata></prolog><refbody class="- topic/body        reference/refbody "><section id="M148565-B32" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Specifications</title><p class="- topic/p ">The following conditions have been defined for both Printhead packages, single pack (spare part) and 4-pack (for installation):</p><table id="GUID-F098965F-FD8D-4FEE-B6DD-F1A2052D7A0C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="70*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Subject</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Specification</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Transport</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Temperature: between -25 and 60 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Celsius (between -13 and 140 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Fahrenheit)</p><p class="- topic/p "> Humidity: between 5 and 95%.</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Storage</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Temperature: between 10 and 40 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Celsius (between 50 and 104 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0 
</sup>Fahrenheit). We highly recommend storage at ~20 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Celsius (~68 
<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">0</sup> Fahrenheit)</p><p class="- topic/p "> Humidity: between 5 and 95%.</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "/><p class="- topic/p ">A sticker on the outside of the single Printhead package shows the storage conditions:</p><fig id="GUID-9AF82385-085D-4821-AC99-F97BB2FD0E79" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A3A9CEBF-68A2-4630-BAAB-A27A841ACF08-low.jpg" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A3A9CEBF-68A2-4630-BAAB-A27A841ACF08-low.jpg"/></fig></section></refbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-FEBAF722-242B-49D6-B670-B3AA1CB42C4A.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Specifications</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
